                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d368">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/594</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-20T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 20, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1149. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_OWH1">Owen</persName> [from War
                    Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 73. Legation’s 2760, September 2, 7 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d368fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> The entire number of ships agreed to be chartered to the
                    United States Shipping Board under the terms of the Swedish agreement now having
                    been placed at the disposal of the United States, we have authorized the
                    issuance of bunker licenses for free Swedish vessels in accordance with
                    provision of the Swedish agreement and subject to the rules and regulations of
                    the War Trade Board. Repeat to London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
